track_notes: 3.8 mile hike with 1200 EG and 560 EL.  Lots of parking at the eastern parking area (35.1578, -82.9989) for Panthertown valley, but it can fill up quickly.  Hike down the Panthertown Valley trail (474) and take a right on the Devils Elbow trail (448) at mile 1.  Around mile 1.91, take a right on an unmarked trail just before the Devils Elbow trail crosses the Little Green Creek.  There were several colors of flagging marking the start of the trail and it turned out that the trail up the creek was quite nice and easy to follow contrary to accounts read online.  At 2.94 miles take a right and follow the trail 0.4 miles.  At this point, take a left up the steep hill (continuing straight will take you into private land).  This trail will take to you to High Bethel, a nice overlook on Caanan Land property (but not posted).  From here to the summit is brushy and densely forested.

9 mile hike with 2200 EG and 2200 EL. Hike down the Panthertown Valley trail (474) and take a right on the Devils Elbow trail (448) at mile 1.  Around mile 1.91, take a right on an unmarked trail just before the Devils Elbow trail crosses the Little Green Creek.  There were several colors of flagging marking the start of the trail and it turned out that the trail up the creek was quite nice and easy to follow contrary to accounts read online.  At 2.94 miles take a right and follow the trail 0.4 miles.  At this point, take a left up the steep hill (continuing straight will take you into private land).  This trail will take to you to High Bethel, a nice overlook on Caanan Land property (but not posted).  From here to the summit is brushy and densely forested.  On the return trip, continue straight instead of following the creek back.  In 0.1 miles turn left and follow all the way back to the Devils Elbow trail.
